# Points, Rewards & Business Settings (theory only)

## Dynamic Business Parameters (Theory)
- All numeric values that drive business logic must be **configurable**, not hardcoded. They are read from a single conceptual **Business Settings** area (no implementation detail).
- This includes: **point amounts** per event type, **commission** (default and overrides), **tax** rate, **user level thresholds** (e.g. 150, 700, 7000), **level discount** percentages (e.g. 5%, 10%), and any similar parameters in business rules.
- When implementing "dynamic points system" or "business settings", code must use these settings as the single source of truth; changing a value in settings must change behavior without code change.

## Points & Rewards — Event Types and Logic (Theory)
- Points are awarded to the **user** (account holder). **Sum of points** determines **user level**, **level discount**, and **rating power**.
- Each eligible event grants points **at most once** per occurrence (except where explicitly defined, e.g. each "collection like" grants once per like).
- **Point amounts** for each event type are defined in Business Settings (dynamic). The logic below describes **when** and **to whom** points are granted.

| Event | Recipient | Condition |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| **Booking leader** | Order owner (buyer) | After order completed (e.g. thank-you / payment confirmed). One grant per order (not per line item), unless design says per product with deduplication. |
| **Teammate** | Registered user whose phone is in the order as teammate | Only if that phone maps to an **existing registered user**. One grant per teammate per order. Users not registered do not receive points. |
| **Game review (comment)** | User who submitted the review | Must have completed a booking for that game; submit within allowed window (e.g. 90 min after slot start, up to 1 week); respect "one comment per game per user". One grant per valid review. |
| **Create collection** | User who created the collection | One grant per new collection created. |
| **Collection liked** | **Owner of the collection** (not the liker) | One grant per like received on their collection. |
| **Registration** | New user | Once per user lifetime when account is created. |
| **Profile completed** | User who completed profile | Once per user lifetime when profile is marked complete (business-defined criteria). |

## Rules to Enforce
- **Leader:** Points only to order owner; one grant per order (or per product with clear deduplication if designed).
- **Teammate:** Points only when teammate phone matches a registered user; one grant per such teammate per order.
- **Review:** Points only for reviews that satisfy game-comment rules (buyer, time window, one per game).
- **Collection:** Fixed logic per "create collection" event; count of collections may be used for description/display only.
- **Collection like:** Recipient = collection owner; liker does not receive points.
- **Registration and profile completed:** At most one grant per user per lifetime; use a flag or equivalent to prevent duplicate grants.

## What Does Not Grant Points
- Teammate without a registered account → no teammate points.
- Review not approved or outside game-comment window/rules → no review points.
- Completing profile again after first time → no extra profile-completed points.
- Duplicate registration for same user → only one registration grant.

## Consistency with Level and Features
- User level is computed only from **sum of points** (thresholds from Business Settings).
- Level discount and rating power are defined by level; feature access (collection, invitation, like, bio, avatar) is gated by level and caps. Points logic must not contradict these.
